1
00:00:00,570 --> 00:00:02,390

2
00:00:03,810 --> 00:00:10,820

3
00:00:16,840 --> 00:00:19,570
Miss Woo Joo?

4
00:00:19,570 --> 00:00:21,400
How did you—

5
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:23,430
How did you know to come here?

6
00:00:23,430 --> 00:00:27,200
I came because I thought I couldn't ever say it if I didn't say it now.

7
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:33,890
You were right, doctor.

8
00:00:34,710 --> 00:00:36,680
I'm a patient.

9
00:00:38,180 --> 00:00:40,690
Please treat me.

10
00:00:41,480 --> 00:00:43,900
You can treat me, right?

11
00:00:47,180 --> 00:00:50,770
I... have no family,

12
00:00:50,770 --> 00:00:53,750
and Gong Ji Sun is my only friend.

13
00:00:53,750 --> 00:00:57,540
I've never ended on good terms with people I've met on stage.

14
00:00:57,540 --> 00:01:01,100
They all disliked me because I'm a fighter.

15
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:04,500
In order to try to get along with others,

16
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:08,090
I've always been wary of them and given them everything I could.

17
00:01:09,710 --> 00:01:12,980
It makes sense... that my boyfriend cheated on me.

18
00:01:12,980 --> 00:01:17,570
Right? Who would like someone like me?

19
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:24,490
You told me that once I acknowledge that I'm sick, I can get treatment.

20
00:01:30,330 --> 00:01:32,720
- Miss Woo Joo... 
 - Yes?

21
00:01:32,720 --> 00:01:37,940
I'm really hungry. Can we get some food first?

22
00:01:47,090 --> 00:01:50,350
 Can you really eat in this situation?

23
00:01:53,410 --> 00:01:57,070
I didn't know you did a podcast.

24
00:01:59,710 --> 00:02:03,040
But, what kind of scar is that?

25
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:05,700
There, on your wrist.

26
00:02:06,810 --> 00:02:08,740
Oh, this?

27
00:02:09,650 --> 00:02:12,050
It was just out of curiosity.

28
00:02:12,050 --> 00:02:14,360
- Did you want to die? 
 - No.

29
00:02:15,470 --> 00:02:18,250
I've never thought that I wanted to die.

30
00:02:18,250 --> 00:02:20,950
I've actually always wanted to survive.

31
00:02:22,050 --> 00:02:26,480
Even when I was tired to death of failing all my auditions,

32
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:29,650
I've always wanted to live,

33
00:02:29,650 --> 00:02:32,420
getting love and attention from others.

34
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:38,060
This was also... another way I tried to get some attention.

35
00:02:38,060 --> 00:02:44,060
It wasn't even with a knife. I was scared it would hurt, so I used a ruler. A plastic ruler.

36
00:02:44,060 --> 00:02:46,700
It ended up scarring because the ruler broke...

37
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:49,020
Why did you want attention?

38
00:02:49,020 --> 00:02:52,630
Isn't everyone like that? Don't you want attention?

39
00:02:52,630 --> 00:02:55,600
I don't. I really don't like it when people pay attention to me.

40
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:58,340
How full of yourself...

41
00:02:58,340 --> 00:02:59,380
Do you remember Cha Dong Il?

42
00:02:59,380 --> 00:03:01,720
How could I forget that fake cop?

43
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:05,580
These days, he's working so hard to prepare for the police exam.

44
00:03:05,580 --> 00:03:07,760
Even if it rains or snows, he goes to the library daily.

45
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:10,770
Goodness... Isn't that so surprising?

46
00:03:10,770 --> 00:03:13,750
So what? What does that have to do with me?

47
00:03:13,750 --> 00:03:15,040
Why wouldn't it have something to do with you?

48
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:17,100
Someone's life was changed because of you.

49
00:03:17,100 --> 00:03:19,110
Because of me? Yeah, right!

50
00:03:19,110 --> 00:03:21,290
Sung Min Ho, who was suffering from anxiety,

51
00:03:21,290 --> 00:03:26,030
was able to say everything he's been keeping to himself for all these years because of you.

52
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:33,130
You are not someone who deserves to be cheated on by their boyfriend.

53
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:37,450
You're someone who changes the lives of others.

54
00:03:39,290 --> 00:03:45,100
There are no conditions that lack a source. There's a reason you must have become a fighter.

55
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:47,110
Now, shall we?

56
00:03:47,110 --> 00:03:48,790
All of a sudden?

57
00:03:48,790 --> 00:03:51,660
Today marks day 1.

58
00:03:51,660 --> 00:03:54,830
I'm your primary physician, and you are my patient.

59
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:05,810
You can't be the kind of bad doctor that quits halfway because it gets difficult, okay?

60
00:04:05,810 --> 00:04:08,870
Listen to what I say and don't even think of running away.

61
00:04:09,830 --> 00:04:11,420
Okay.

62
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:49,780
Boop!

63
00:04:49,780 --> 00:04:52,800
Let's see...

64
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:56,030
 For the time being, the weather will be clear.

65
00:04:56,030 --> 00:04:57,590
 That concludes the weather forecast.

66
00:04:57,590 --> 00:05:00,400
 Today was yet another eventful day.

67
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:03,860
 In times like this, it's good to take a break and go

68
00:05:03,860 --> 00:05:05,290
 look at the cherry blossoms with your loved one.

69
00:05:05,290 --> 00:05:08,640
Cherry blossoms? Yeah, right!

70
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:09,940
 I'm Hwang Min Wook.

71
00:05:09,940 --> 00:05:13,950
Wait a minute. Why is he still wearing the watch that I gave him?

72
00:05:36,330 --> 00:05:38,250
- Hello? 
 - It's been a while.

73
00:05:38,250 --> 00:05:41,110
Give me back the watch. You don't deserve to wear that watch.

74
00:05:41,110 --> 00:05:43,400
I bet you don't even know what kind of watch that is.

75
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:47,970
That watch doesn't belong on the wrist of a bastard like you!

76
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:51,330
What?

77
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:56,670
In a package? Do you really want to die?

78
00:05:56,670 --> 00:06:01,200
Forget it. I'm going to get it right now, so you wait right there.

79
00:06:02,450 --> 00:06:05,640
The watch... Goodness!

80
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:25,280
 That watch doesn't belong on the wrist of a bastard like you!

81
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:27,970
  Do you really want to die?

82
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:30,620
What have I done this time?

83
00:06:32,180 --> 00:06:34,930
You pathetic psycho.

84
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:39,350
Why are you like this?

85
00:07:01,510 --> 00:07:02,800
 Did you want to die?

86
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:06,450
 No. I've never thought that I wanted to die.

87
00:07:06,450 --> 00:07:09,230
 I've actually always wanted to survive.

88
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:13,790
 What makes her want to live so badly?

89
00:07:15,910 --> 00:07:18,310

90
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:22,920
Just let him be for now. Don't take your eyes off him.

91
00:07:34,250 --> 00:07:37,370
New York, Paris, Tokyo, anywhere everyone's going!

92
00:07:37,370 --> 00:07:44,280
New York, Paris, Tokyo, anywhere everyone's going!

93
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:48,030
Anywhere! Anywhere everyone's going!

94
00:07:48,030 --> 00:07:52,480
Go, go, go, go! Go!

95
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,960
Go! Go!

96
00:07:58,490 --> 00:08:02,250
 Anywhere everyone's going. Everyone's going.

97
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:04,980
Are you just going to keep watching him like that?

98
00:08:04,980 --> 00:08:07,520
 Tokyo. Anywhere everyone's going.

99
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:10,370
His current medication doesn't seem to be working.

100
00:08:10,370 --> 00:08:14,840
I think you should give him a different drug with greater sedating effects.

101
00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:16,760
 Anywhere everyone's going.

102
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:19,560
If you give the order, I will move immediately.

103
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:21,460
Please wait a moment.

104
00:08:21,460 --> 00:08:23,500
Dr. Lee is on his way.

105
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:27,160
If all the other patients wake up because of him, we'll be in bigger trouble.

106
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:28,210
 Anywhere, everyone's going.

107
00:08:28,210 --> 00:08:31,000
Ru Oh's symptoms are getting worse.

108
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,420
Eventually, he won't eat or sleep,

109
00:08:33,420 --> 00:08:35,770
and just lay there like a dead person.

110
00:08:35,770 --> 00:08:39,240
When Doctor Lee gets here, I'll let you know.

111
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,960
Dr. Lee.

112
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:50,240
 Anywhere where everyone's going.

113
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:52,490
His visual hallucinations have gotten worse.

114
00:08:52,490 --> 00:08:54,900
Should we increase his dosage?

115
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:57,770
Dr. Oh suggested we could change to a heavier sedative—

116
00:08:57,770 --> 00:09:00,720
You said his condition got worse. Why would we increase his dosage if it got worse?

117
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:03,730
Dr. Lee, he has to sleep.

118
00:09:03,730 --> 00:09:08,560
He's been like this anytime he eats. It's hard for us and the patient.

119
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:10,500
His ability to recognize faces has decreased tremendously as well.

120
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:13,430
I'm going to take Ru Oh on a walk.

121
00:09:13,430 --> 00:09:16,340
What? At this hour?

122
00:09:16,340 --> 00:09:17,420
Dr. Lee...

123
00:09:17,420 --> 00:09:18,860
You can't take him on a walk.

124
00:09:18,860 --> 00:09:23,440
Per the hospital's rules, night walks with patients are prohibited.

125
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:25,430
I'll stick right next to him.

126
00:09:25,430 --> 00:09:29,240
If you let him take a walk now, his sleep cycle will be affected as well.

127
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:32,920
- New York, Paris, Tokyo. Anywhere where everyone's going. 
 - Park Ru Oh?

128
00:09:33,920 --> 00:09:36,280
Shall we go on a walk?

129
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:46,240
Ru Oh seems to be in a better mood now.

130
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:48,570
It must've been stuffy in his ward.

131
00:09:48,570 --> 00:09:50,840
He first started having hallucinations

132
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:54,790
in the student dormitory he lived in after he came to Korea. 
 (T/N: Affordable, but very cramped, rooms for students.)

133
00:09:54,790 --> 00:09:59,500
His symptoms may have gotten worse because his hospital ward is small.

134
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:02,680
That's why you suggested... a walk.

135
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:18,870
I wonder how the mind of a 15 year-old became so complicated.

136
00:10:18,870 --> 00:10:22,760
But Doctor... is it okay to break the rules like this?

137
00:10:22,760 --> 00:10:25,160
Dr. Oh seemed really angry.

138
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:27,530
That's why I suggested we take a walk.

139
00:10:27,530 --> 00:10:28,610
What?

140
00:10:28,610 --> 00:10:33,180
Whenever she sees me, she just spits poison, so I ran away.

141
00:10:35,380 --> 00:10:36,860
Ru-Ru Oh!

142
00:10:36,860 --> 00:10:38,270
Hey, Ru Oh!

143
00:10:38,270 --> 00:10:41,260
Ru Oh! Where are you going?

144
00:10:41,260 --> 00:10:42,640
Ru Oh!

145
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:44,510
If I catch you, you're in trouble!

146
00:10:44,510 --> 00:10:46,380
Ru Oh, be careful!

147
00:10:46,380 --> 00:10:48,030
Ru Oh, where are you going?

148
00:10:48,030 --> 00:10:50,020
Hey, watch the stairs! They're dangerous!

149
00:10:50,020 --> 00:10:53,030
You're going to get hurt!

150
00:10:55,710 --> 00:10:57,600
Gosh, he's so fast.

151
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:59,560
Ru Oh!

152
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:47,690
 Symptoms getting worse.

153
00:11:52,030 --> 00:11:56,040
 Visual hallucinations getting worse, facial recognition...

154
00:12:00,390 --> 00:12:03,260
The mental health center seems like it will open sooner than we expected.

155
00:12:03,260 --> 00:12:05,240
Really?

156
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:12,330
Dr. In, be honest. Who do you think will be the center's first director?

157
00:12:12,330 --> 00:12:15,730
Can I really be honest?

158
00:12:15,730 --> 00:12:18,730
Of course.

159
00:12:18,730 --> 00:12:24,130
I think... Chief Park will take that position.

160
00:12:24,130 --> 00:12:26,400
Aren't you being a little too honest?

161
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:29,490
I personally hope you will take the position because

162
00:12:29,490 --> 00:12:34,520
I want the new mental health center to use your treatment methods.

163
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:39,780
Of course, this is because I'm following in your footsteps as well.

164
00:12:39,780 --> 00:12:41,030
Are you being sincere?

165
00:12:41,030 --> 00:12:44,380
You know how honest I was just now.

166
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:48,300
Then I think you'll need to help me a bit.

167
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:49,900
With what should I help you?

168
00:12:49,900 --> 00:12:55,060
Find Lee Si Joon's weakness. Something that will deter Chief Park.

169
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:05,090
Did you know that Chief Park and the President of the hospital went to the same school?

170
00:13:05,090 --> 00:13:07,640
I didn't know that.

171
00:13:09,230 --> 00:13:12,570
I'm not trying to become the center's director because I want the position.

172
00:13:12,570 --> 00:13:17,060
I'm a doctor too. I have the patient's interest in mind, just like anyone else.

173
00:13:17,060 --> 00:13:21,860
The center will fail if it takes after the approach of Chief Park and Lee Si Joon.

174
00:13:22,670 --> 00:13:26,900
People seem to not know this, but mental illnesses are infectious.

175
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:30,330
Just look at how many patients have panic attacks these days.

176
00:13:30,330 --> 00:13:35,810
The number will only increase from here. Using Lee Si Joon's methods? There's no chance.

177
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:39,620
Will you help me?

178
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:45,600
Well, sure. I'll help you,

179
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:48,210
for the mental health center.

180
00:13:48,210 --> 00:13:53,810
Alright. Let's work hard for the mental health of this country.

181
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:23,650
I understand. I'll make sure I have a word with Dr. Lee.

182
00:14:23,650 --> 00:14:29,070
Now that I've told you this, I actually feel a little uneasy.

183
00:14:29,070 --> 00:14:33,750
I know that Dr. Lee cares for his patients more than anyone,

184
00:14:33,750 --> 00:14:35,660
but we need to survive as well.

185
00:14:35,660 --> 00:14:39,740
Patients need to sleep at night, but he never sleeps.

186
00:14:39,740 --> 00:14:42,350
I understand.

187
00:14:42,350 --> 00:14:48,970
At this rate, the nurses in this ward may leave in protest.

188
00:14:48,970 --> 00:14:51,680
To be honest, in cases as extreme as patient Park,

189
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:56,570
it's better for the patient as well to put him to sleep, even if that means forcing him to take the sedatives.

190
00:14:56,570 --> 00:15:00,610
He's on the brink of entering a vegetative state. I think giving him strong sedati—

191
00:15:00,610 --> 00:15:05,760
Doctor. You've said enough.

192
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:11,150
The primary physician will decide what specific drug to prescribe the patient.

193
00:15:11,990 --> 00:15:15,990
I've crossed the line. I apologize.

194
00:15:18,030 --> 00:15:20,030
I'll be leaving now.

195
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:36,970
Ru Oh's mother.

196
00:15:38,010 --> 00:15:39,500
You want to discharge Ru Oh?

197
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:42,890
It's time for us to return to Vietnam.

198
00:15:42,890 --> 00:15:48,210
If he just finishes one more semester there, he can attend college there as a foreign exchange student.

199
00:15:48,210 --> 00:15:50,140
It's the reason we've stayed there this long.

200
00:15:50,140 --> 00:15:53,740
It would be such a loss to just give up like this.

201
00:15:53,740 --> 00:15:55,640
Ru Oh cannot be discharged from the hospital.

202
00:15:55,640 --> 00:16:00,180
Why can't I discharge my child from the hospital when I'd like?

203
00:16:00,180 --> 00:16:02,280
He's gotten worse.

204
00:16:02,280 --> 00:16:03,310
Why?

205
00:16:03,310 --> 00:16:05,710
We'll look into the source of that from here on out.

206
00:16:05,710 --> 00:16:11,660
What am I supposed to think if he's only gotten worse after being here for three months?

207
00:16:11,660 --> 00:16:18,870
Three months is nothing compared to the time he spent in isolation.

208
00:16:20,060 --> 00:16:25,340
Are you suggesting this all happened because I left my son in isolation?

209
00:16:25,340 --> 00:16:29,150
Do you think I wanted to make my child live in a tiny student dormitory?

210
00:16:29,150 --> 00:16:32,230
My child left school and was being called a returnee—

211
00:16:32,230 --> 00:16:34,500

212
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:35,880
without my knowledge.

213
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:41,460
I mean to say that, as a doctor, I need more time to fully treat Ru Oh.

214
00:16:41,460 --> 00:16:46,900
Are you confident that you can fix my son?

215
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:50,970
I'm asking you if you're confident.

216
00:16:50,970 --> 00:16:53,980
♪  This is love  ♪

217
00:16:53,980 --> 00:16:56,410
Everyone, please follow me.

218
00:16:56,410 --> 00:16:58,110
Okay!

219
00:16:58,110 --> 00:17:00,640
From now on!

220
00:17:00,640 --> 00:17:03,290
Forget about all your pain!

