Dr. Lee!

257
00:20:37,820 --> 00:20:40,370
Doctor, what should I do? I caused big trouble yesterday.

258
00:20:40,370 --> 00:20:42,560
What kind of trouble?

259
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:49,710
I couldn't see anything else then. I could only see the watch.

260
00:20:49,710 --> 00:20:55,020
I could only think that watch is something that person shouldn't be wearing.

261
00:20:55,020 --> 00:20:58,920
So you called him right away and asked for it back?

262
00:20:59,900 --> 00:21:04,820
I learned for the first time that a person could be as petty as this.

263
00:21:04,820 --> 00:21:10,320
Because of that, my rising self-confidence hit rock bottom,

264
00:21:10,320 --> 00:21:12,270
and I even feel kind of depressed.

265
00:21:12,270 --> 00:21:16,370
- Was it expensive? 
 - Yes. Incredibly.

266
00:21:16,370 --> 00:21:19,860
I bought it for him to celebrate my first leading role.

267
00:21:19,860 --> 00:21:22,030
Now that I think about it, it's kind of pathetic.

268
00:21:22,030 --> 00:21:25,370
Why would I buy him a watch in celebration of me landing the leading role?

269
00:21:25,370 --> 00:21:28,440
I should be the one receiving congratulations.

270
00:21:30,750 --> 00:21:36,700
After I bought that for him, I was broke and walked around looking like a beggar.

271
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:38,710
I was suddenly so upset by that thought.

272
00:21:38,710 --> 00:21:42,890
I suffered like that to buy someone like him a nice watch?

273
00:21:42,890 --> 00:21:45,490
You did very well.

274
00:21:45,490 --> 00:21:48,990
- What? 
 - Go get that watch back.

275
00:21:48,990 --> 00:21:50,720
If you're upset at something, you should resolve it.

276
00:21:50,720 --> 00:21:54,680
That's true, but... this is seriously petty.

277
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:57,920
Dating always ends in pettiness.

278
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:59,470
Make sure you get that watch, okay?

279
00:21:59,470 --> 00:22:02,190
- Really? 
 - Call me once you get it back.

280
00:22:05,870 --> 00:22:09,410

281
00:22:13,930 --> 00:22:17,430
What do you think? Is it to your liking?

282
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:20,760
The facilities are not the main issue right now.

283
00:22:20,760 --> 00:22:25,960
It's the first mental health center in Korea being opened by a university hospital.

284
00:22:25,960 --> 00:22:30,850
To be honest, I am very excited.

285
00:22:30,850 --> 00:22:33,300
What are you the most excited about?

286
00:22:33,300 --> 00:22:37,170
I'm excited that there will be so many more hospital rooms available for patients.

287
00:22:37,170 --> 00:22:42,710
I'm also excited for the trauma center and the establishment of the suicide prevention help line.

288
00:22:42,710 --> 00:22:44,800
I'm excited for all of it.

289
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:49,490
Korea is a country with many wounds.

290
00:22:49,490 --> 00:22:54,110
You know I was at the site of 9/11 in America?

291
00:22:54,110 --> 00:22:56,230
Yes, of course.

292
00:22:56,230 --> 00:23:02,220
At the time, the biggest concern of the U.S. government was establishing a trauma center.

293
00:23:02,220 --> 00:23:07,580
The survivors as well as the family members of individuals who didn't survive the incident all got treatment.

294
00:23:09,190 --> 00:23:12,880
I also received a lot of help from that center as well.

295
00:23:14,140 --> 00:23:17,400
But then I realized Korea didn't have a place like that.

296
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:22,440
Our bridges fall, passenger boats sink, and the subways collapse.

297
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:26,980
There are big accidents happening all over the country,

298
00:23:26,980 --> 00:23:32,620
but they want us to just endure it. Forget about it. Does that make sense?

299
00:23:32,620 --> 00:23:39,530
This place has many wounds, but not enough healing.

300
00:23:39,530 --> 00:23:42,400
That must be your reason.

301
00:23:43,690 --> 00:23:46,830
The reason you want to establish the mental health center.

302
00:23:46,830 --> 00:23:48,900
Chief Park, you're still...

303
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:52,900
quite naive, as you've always been.

304
00:23:53,940 --> 00:23:55,670
Am I?

305
00:23:58,480 --> 00:24:00,370
Hello?

306
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:07,840
Yes, thank you for letting me know.

307
00:24:07,840 --> 00:24:10,710
Let's meet up soon, okay?

308
00:24:14,470 --> 00:24:18,160
They say an investigation team is coming with a search warrant.

309
00:24:18,160 --> 00:24:23,540
- To our department? 
 - Someone must have made a report to the National Human Rights Institution.

310
00:24:23,540 --> 00:24:26,590
They said there was a case of violence in the hospital wards.

311
00:24:36,980 --> 00:24:39,190
What's that?

312
00:24:39,190 --> 00:24:41,630
I'll head in first.

313
00:24:53,930 --> 00:24:56,970
We're the investigation team from the Seoul Metropolitan Police.

314
00:24:56,970 --> 00:24:58,360
What?

315
00:24:59,590 --> 00:25:02,590
We will be conducting a search and seizure investigation.

316
00:25:02,590 --> 00:25:03,840
A sei—

317
00:25:03,840 --> 00:25:05,950
For what reason?

318
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:12,460
Someone reported that a patient was forcefully admitted into an asylum and treated with violence.

319
00:25:12,460 --> 00:25:16,270
We'll be taking materials from February 1st of last year

320
00:25:16,270 --> 00:25:19,270
pertaining to the patient's records and any relevant CCTV material.

321
00:25:19,270 --> 00:25:20,640
Please begin.

322
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:22,710
We object to the search.

323
00:25:22,710 --> 00:25:26,710
A doctor has a responsibility to protect the records of their patient.

324
00:25:28,590 --> 00:25:30,590
Doctor Lee.

325
00:25:40,120 --> 00:25:43,830
If you continue acting like this, you could be arrested for noncompliance.

326
00:25:43,830 --> 00:25:46,830
A report has already been made to the National Human Rights Institution.

327
00:25:46,830 --> 00:25:50,680
Are you not aware that you must comply no matter what to reports made to the National Institution?

328
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:55,330
Are you not aware that doctors must protect no matter what the personal information of their patients?

329
00:25:56,850 --> 00:25:58,970
What are you doing?

330
00:26:05,340 --> 00:26:07,000
Comply to the search.

331
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:08,710
Chief.

332
00:26:08,710 --> 00:26:10,630
It's about patient Park Ru Oh.

333
00:26:10,630 --> 00:26:15,500
- What? 
 - There was concrete evidence filed to the Human Rights Institution.

334
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:17,450
Let them conduct the search.

335
00:26:17,450 --> 00:26:19,490
Please go ahead.

336
00:26:21,230 --> 00:26:27,690

337
00:26:37,930 --> 00:26:40,290
Please only take items that are explicitly granted to you in the search warrant.

338
00:26:40,290 --> 00:26:43,370
Sure, sure. We don't need other materials anyways.

339
00:26:44,220 --> 00:26:47,090
Where are the CCTV record kept in this hospital?

340
00:26:50,830 --> 00:26:52,270
Can't you hear me?

341
00:26:52,270 --> 00:26:55,210
They're stored in the administrative offices.

342
00:26:57,550 --> 00:27:02,600
Do you really have no idea why this happened? The search and seizure.

343
00:27:16,070 --> 00:27:18,550
What's going on?

344
00:27:18,550 --> 00:27:20,840
I'm so worried.

345
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:25,950
You know, right? The reason the search warrant came out?

346
00:27:25,950 --> 00:27:31,450
When Ru Oh first came to the hospital, we couldn't get into contact with his guardians.

347
00:27:31,450 --> 00:27:34,450
It had passed the three-day window where we could admit him as an emergency case.

348
00:27:34,450 --> 00:27:36,330
So?

349
00:27:37,760 --> 00:27:42,350
So I forcefully admitted him, without the consent of a guardian.

350
00:27:42,350 --> 00:27:44,840
I think that became a problem.

351
00:27:52,280 --> 00:27:54,800
 You have to come back with your mother.

352
00:27:54,800 --> 00:28:00,030
 You need more treatment, but we're letting you go because we don't have consent from your guardians.

353
00:28:00,030 --> 00:28:03,830
 - You have to come back, okay? 
 - Thank you.

354
00:28:04,750 --> 00:28:06,480
 Ru Oh, you don't have to leave.

355
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:08,040
 Doctor...

356
00:28:08,040 --> 00:28:11,970
 I got in contact with his guardian. They're getting on a plane from Vietnam right away.

357
00:28:11,970 --> 00:28:15,740
 Don't we still need to let him go for now?

358
00:28:15,740 --> 00:28:17,400
 Let him leave, and then readmit him.

359
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:21,040
 How could you send him back to that tiny student dorm in this condition?

360
00:28:21,040 --> 00:28:23,600
 He's still suffering from visual hallucinations.

361
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:26,330
 Forget it. An extra day won't hurt.

362
00:28:31,270 --> 00:28:35,050
But to be honest, it wasn't just one day.

363
00:28:35,050 --> 00:28:38,500
I remember, the guardian came after a week had passed.

364
00:28:38,500 --> 00:28:42,220
So you knew about all of that even then.

365
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:44,400
He's a 15-year-old schizophrenia patient.

366
00:28:44,400 --> 00:28:51,150
He was showing signs of hallucinatory behavior. I saw him run in front of a car with my own eyes. How could I let him leave?

367
00:28:55,680 --> 00:28:59,880
You must be getting a lot of resentment from others.

368
00:28:59,880 --> 00:29:00,780
What does that mean?

369
00:29:00,780 --> 00:29:04,490
To you, that was the right thing to do. But others must have been uncomfortable about it.

370
00:29:04,490 --> 00:29:10,530
Why else would they anonymously file a complaint now for something that happened three months ago?

371
00:29:10,530 --> 00:29:13,950
Well, if that's the case, there are multiple people like that.

372
00:29:13,950 --> 00:29:15,940
Can you joke in a situation like this?

373
00:29:15,940 --> 00:29:18,590
In this situation, I kind of wish I could drink right now.

374
00:29:19,970 --> 00:29:22,930
Come out after you've resolved everything then.

375
00:29:22,930 --> 00:29:24,760
Are you letting me drink with you tonight?

376
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:27,350
I don't know.

377
00:29:27,350 --> 00:29:29,210
What are you going to buy me? Huh?

378
00:29:29,210 --> 00:29:31,240
What are you going to buy me?

379
00:29:31,240 --> 00:29:34,630
Goodness...

380
00:29:34,630 --> 00:29:38,290
You ordered a good one.

381
00:29:40,920 --> 00:29:45,940
I thought search and seize investigations were only done in cases of illegal possessions or  fraud.

382
00:29:45,940 --> 00:29:49,870
Me too. I didn't think that a psychiatrist could receive a search and seizure order.

383
00:29:49,870 --> 00:29:53,860
It happens more often than you guys may think.

384
00:29:53,860 --> 00:29:56,940
Who would have filed a report to the Human Rights Institute?

385
00:29:56,940 --> 00:29:59,640
Was it the guardian? Usually it's the guardian that does things like this.

386
00:29:59,640 --> 00:30:04,900
Guardians don't usually file a complaint. They would just sue the hospital.

387
00:30:04,900 --> 00:30:11,400
The fact that they made a public report means that they wanted to protect themselves with the anonymity.

388
00:30:12,730 --> 00:30:15,930
Don't you think someone could have done this intentionally?

389
00:30:15,930 --> 00:30:20,070
There's a famous phrase you can use at times like these.

390
00:30:20,070 --> 00:30:22,140
The culprit is closer than you think.

391
00:30:22,140 --> 00:30:24,310
- So who? 
 - Doctor In.

392
00:30:25,800 --> 00:30:29,040
- Goodness. 
 - I'm sorry. Bad joke.

393
00:30:29,040 --> 00:30:34,830
If you file a public complaint, the investigation commences right away. They may have been after that.

394
00:30:34,830 --> 00:30:38,160
It means someone genuinely thought there was some issue.

395
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:41,510
The nurses in the wards did have lots of complaints.

396
00:30:41,510 --> 00:30:44,740
I heard the nurses whispering amongst themselves a lot, too.

397
00:30:44,740 --> 00:30:49,440
They were complaining that the patients wouldn't sleep because Dr. Lee wouldn't prescribe his patients sedatives.

398
00:30:50,180 --> 00:30:55,380
You all should think about whether you might have even accidentally done anything wrong to patient Park Ru Oh.

399
00:30:55,380 --> 00:30:58,570
Another investigation could come out soon.

400
00:30:58,570 --> 00:31:00,610
Yes.

401
00:31:02,780 --> 00:31:06,160
So who would report something like this?

402
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:09,030
Since it's a public report, there's no way for us to find out.

403
00:31:09,030 --> 00:31:11,750
I mean, do things like this happen often?

404
00:31:11,750 --> 00:31:15,800
Once in a while? It happens at other hospitals too.

405
00:31:15,800 --> 00:31:22,970
I think it's been 2 years? One patient sued us as soon as they were discharged from the hospital, claiming they were assaulted.

406
00:31:22,970 --> 00:31:27,100
Thanks to the surveillance cameras, it was revealed that was a lie.

407
00:31:28,270 --> 00:31:32,400
Woo Joo, don't worry. Dr. Lee watched over Ru Oh with so much care.

408
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:37,110
He didn't even prescribe Ru Oh any medication, because his body rejected all of it.

409
00:31:37,110 --> 00:31:41,460
Well, I guess the nurses had to suffer every night because of that.

410
00:31:41,460 --> 00:31:43,680
Someone definitely planned this out.

411
00:31:43,680 --> 00:31:47,540
They're trying to find flaws in Dr. Lee.

412
00:31:47,540 --> 00:31:50,210
I'm going to find out who made the report.
